						<div class="postbody">Well, this should be very common question among the "Newbie Help Center," although, I havn't seen (at a glance) anyone that has asked the question "How can I make a NES rom, and what programs do I need?," so I guess I'll have to ask it. I guess the reason why I'm asking this is because I want to start a sort of project... and the project consists of making a NES game and putting it into it's natural rom format.
<br />
<br />Basically, I need to know what programming language, along with some help in how to write it (like a documentation on the language, and especially what program I should be typing this programming language in). Examples would also help :D.
<br />
<br />Oh, and if there is a such thing, I might also need a disasembler for roms. What better way to learn than to take apart another NES game and see how it works :].
<br />
<br />I would also ask about sprites, music, and how to make them both, but if there is a disassembler, then there would be no need on how to piece them into the rom.
<br />
<br />And if I missed anything that is needed in making a NES rom, please let me know. Again, I'm a "Newbie," so overexplain if possible, and don't be afraid to repeat youself.
<br />
<br />Thanks in advance,
<br />--Cartridge
<br />
<br />(PS: Now that I think of it, I know a way to repay any kind of help. Any basic and extraordinary help will be put into the credits of this game. I'm serious (unless if you don't want me to). It's just that I need serious help, and I want to give credit when due. Thanks again)</div>

					
